                                    {
                                        "amendType": "edit",
                                        "ancestorRefs": [
                                            "28",
                                            "2801"
                                        ],
                                        "body": "The provisions of this chapter, the <em class=\"u-italic\">Mechanical Code<span class=\"code_addition\"> of New York State</span></em> and the <em class=\"u-italic\"><a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/new_york/ny-fuel-gas-code-2020\">Fuel Gas Code</a><span class=\"code_addition\"> of New York State</span></em> shall govern the design, construction, erection and installation of mechanical appliances, equipment and systems used in buildings and structures covered by this code. <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/new_york/ibc-2018/chapter/2/definitions#masonry_\">Masonry</a> <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/new_york/ibc-2018/chapter/2/definitions#chimney_\">chimneys</a>, <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/new_york/ibc-2018/chapter/2/definitions#fireplace_\">fireplaces</a> and barbecues shall comply with the <em class=\"u-italic\">Mechanical Code<span class=\"code_addition\"> of New York State</span></em> and <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/new_york/ibc-2018/chapter/21/masonry#21\">Chapter 21</a> of this code. The <em class=\"u-italic\">Fire Code<span class=\"code_addition\"> of New York State</span></em>, the <em class=\"u-italic\">Property Maintenance Code<span class=\"code_addition\"> of New York State</span></em>, the <em class=\"u-italic\"><a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/new_york/ny-mechanical-code-2020\">Mechanical Code</a><span class=\"code_addition\"> of New York State</span></em> and the <em class=\"u-italic\"><a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/new_york/ny-fuel-gas-code-2020\">Fuel Gas Code</a><span class=\"code_addition\"> of New York State</span></em> shall govern the use and maintenance of mechanical components, appliances, equipment and systems. The <em class=\"u-italic\">Existing Building Code<span class=\"code_addition\"> of New York State</span></em>, the <em class=\"u-italic\"><a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/new_york/ny-mechanical-code-2020\">Mechanical Code</a><span class=\"code_addition\"> of New York State</span></em> and the <em class=\"u-italic\"><a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/new_york/ny-fuel-gas-code-2020\">Fuel Gas Code</a><span class=\"code_addition\"> of New York State</span></em> shall govern the <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/new_york/ibc-2018/chapter/2/definitions#alteration_\">alteration</a>, <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/new_york/ibc-2018/chapter/2/definitions#repair_\">repair</a>, relocation, replacement and <a class=\"autolink\" href=\"/viewer/new_york/ibc-2018/chapter/2/definitions#addition_\">addition</a> of mechanical components, appliances, equipment and systems.",
                                        "depth": 2,
