                                            {
                                                "key": "equipment_clr_from_grade",
                                                "title": "Equipment and Appliance Clearances from Grade",
                                                "descriptionHtml": "<div>Where an appliance or piece of equipment is installed at grade level, such as a basement or crawl space, the code has installation clearance requirements.  If the equipment or appliance is to be suspended it must be at least 6\" above adjoining grade and supported in accordance wit the manufacturer's installation instructions.  If the equipment or appliance will be floor mounted, it must be placed on a level concrete slab or other approved material that extends at least 3\" above the adjoining grade.</div>",
                                                "topics": [
                                                    "Mechanical"
                                                ],
