                                                ],
                                                "supressesChildrenAssociations": false,
                                                "blacklistJurisdictions": [],
                                                "whitelistJurisdictions": [],
                                                "imageType": "svg"
                                            },
                                            {
                                                "key": "appliance_access",
                                                "title": "Appliance Access",
                                                "descriptionHtml": "<div>A work space at least 30\" wide by 30\" deep must be provided immediately in front of the appliance's controls. Access to appliances needs to allow for the appliance to be inspected, operated, serviced and/or replaced without the removal of or disabling the function of any of the following:\n<ul><li>Fire-resistance rated assembly</li>\n<li>Permanent Construction such as walls, floors and ceilings</li>\n<li>Other appliances</li>\n<li>Venting systems, Ducts or Pipes not connected to the appliance</li></ul></div>",
                                                "topics": [
                                                    "Mechanical"
                                                ],
                                                "phases": [
                                                    "Construction Docs"
                                                ],
                                                "supressesChildrenAssociations": false,
                                                "blacklistJurisdictions": [],
                                                "whitelistJurisdictions": [],
                                                "imageType": "svg"
                                            },
                                            {
                                                "key": "fuel_fired_app_parking_garage",
                                                "title": "Fuel-Fired Appliances at Parking Garages",
                                                "descriptionHtml": "<div>Any room containing a fuel-fired appliance is required to be separated from a private garage by a 2 doorways and a vestibule. Where the ignition source of the appliance is elevated 18\" from the garage floor in accordance with section 304.3 a single door is permitted. For public garage see section 304.6.</div>",
                                                "topics": [
                                                    "Mechanical"
                                                ],
                                                "phases": [
                                                    "Construction Docs",
                                                    "Construction Phase"
                                                ],
                                                "supressesChildrenAssociations": false,
                                                "blacklistJurisdictions": [],
                                                "whitelistJurisdictions": [],
                                                "imageType": "svg"
                                            },
                                            {
                                                "key": "ducts_weather_protection",
                                                "title": "Weather Protection of Ducts",
                                                "descriptionHtml": "<div>Exterior ducts including  linings, insulation, coverings and vibration isolation are required to be protected from the elements.  If the exterior duct is insulated the duct's protection against the elements must be an approved weatherproof barrier.</div>",
